description:
Work closely and provide day-to-day administrative support to internal teams
Assisting the Retail team to deliver the effective store operations service
Provide daily operations support to all shops, including stock inventory control, customer service enquiry, manpower planning, periodic stock take and any other ad hoc project
Responsible for handling phone, email, fax, WhatsApp's customer service enquiry, concerning pre-sales & after-sales issues
Handle customer relations and complaints
Help improve standard operation flow and assist in any ad-hoc project when necessary

Requirements

Higher Diploma holder or above is preferred;
A self-confident, customer-oriented, outgoing energetic team player with a good learning attitude is preferred;
Able to multi-task, adaptive to a fast-changing environment;
Proficiency in generic computer skills;
Experience in Retail operation and e-commerce is preferred;
Fresh Graduates are Welcome

The Role:

You will be a member of the Global Product Innovation Team of the Logitech Creativity & Productivity Business Group (from Feb 2022 to July 2022 for 6 months). Based in Hong Kong, your main role will be to support and drive new product development projects/programs. Working in a multi-functional environment, across several Logitech sites around the world, you will get a truly international experience. 

Your Contribution:
These are some of the winning behaviors you’ll need for success at Logitech.
Move fast -  Speak up -  Decide and own -  Drive change -  Exceed customer needs 
In this role you will:

Participate in front-end innovation projects to identify new and valuable opportunities to develop meaningful and relevant product innovations;

Drive necessary research to support product definition and development;

Build and test concept hardware/software prototype with consumer to provide recommendations to the PM;

Review hardware/software prototypes to improve the product experience;

Be involved in close collaboration with engineering, portfolio and design teams.

Key Qualifications:
For consideration, you must bring the following minimum skills and behaviors to our team:

Major in Computer Science or Product Design or Social Science or Marketing and Communication with an understanding of business and/or human studies, etc;

Experience in hardware and/or software. UX design experience a plus

Creativity and problem solving oriented, with a strong entrepreneurial mindset;

Ability to thrive in a multi-disciplinary environment and to effectively collaborate in cross functional teams;

Customer centric approach: strong ability to empathize with the user and user challenges and tensions

Excellent communication (oral & written) skills – English & Mandarin required.

Logitech is the sweet spot for people who are passionate about products, making a mark, and having fun doing it. As a company, we’re small and flexible enough for every person to take initiative and make things happen. But we’re big enough in our portfolio, and reach, for those actions to have a global impact. That’s a pretty sweet spot to be in and we’re always striving to keep it that way.


